public void getActionsender().sendCreateObject(26838, 3165, 3486, 0, -1, 10); {
  1. That’s not how you declare a void. Maybe try this?

public void loadObjects() { getActionsender().sendCreateObject(26838, 3165, 3486, 0, -1, 10); }

Change the “loadObjects” to anything you like, and make sure you have the sendCreateObject(int, int, int, int, int, int) working. That will hopefully load the object created using the sendCreateObject. If you have any errors, please post. I’m not too sure this will work.
